rom the rigid principles of Protestant political exclusionism by challenging the fundamental tenets of English constitutional order. The attempt to bring English law, religion, and custom to Quebec forced the State to revise its whole approach to the existing political and religious problems of the day. In forming his argument, Lawson has made use of material which has recently come to light.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356200440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773562004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773562004/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles